data.description: Welcome to this 4 bedroom, 2 full bath mid-century modern home in the heart of Springfield Township. Step inside and you’re greeted by the quintessential mid-century open concept living and dining area with expansive windows, skylights and beautiful built-in wooden shelving. A gas fireplace with schist stone surround is the anchor of this lovely, light-filled space. Original hardwood floors run throughout, currently preserved beneath  wall to wall carpeting. Take a  look in the extra deep entryway closet to  confirm the beauty of the flooring. The pristine vintage eat-in kitchen kitchen with beautiful deep bay picture window is spacious and conveniently includes the washer and dryer behind sliding doors and a full bath with shower. Off the living room are three bedrooms, one of which boasts built-in shelving and another with acoustic tiles for sound management. The hall bath was extended and includes a large soaking tub/shower combo and a skylight. The fourth bedroom, with a lovely bay window is located off the entryway and has an entire wall of built-in closets/storage. Perfect for guests, an older child or a home office. This home is situated back from the street on a beautifully landscaped near half acre lot with additional common space beyond the fence and a 1-car garage. Mature trees, flowering dogwoods, rhododendron and azaleas abound and the yard is almost fully fenced. Enjoy the beauty from the patio with retractable awning. The full basement has plenty of room for storage and has been equipped with a sump pump and french drain. Exceptional location near Springfield High School, Ft. Washington State Park, recreational clubs featuring golf and tennis, 1.3 miles from Oreland regional rail station and convenient to major roadways including Route 309 and the turnpike. Finally a mid-century modern home at a price you can afford! Photos with furniture have been digitally staged.
